theorem dense_iff_interior_closure_eq_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A ↔ interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hDense
    exact interior_closure_eq_univ_of_dense (A := A) hDense
  · intro hInt
    -- Show that `closure A = univ`, whence `A` is dense.
    have hClosureUniv : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      apply subset_antisymm
      · intro _ _; trivial
      · intro x hx_univ
        -- Use `hInt` to turn `x ∈ univ` into `x ∈ interior (closure A)`,
        -- then use `interior_subset` to land in `closure A`.
        have : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure A) := by
          simpa [hInt] using hx_univ
        exact interior_subset this
    exact ⟨hClosureUniv⟩
